snippet.title: Predictions for 2022 (published in 1922)
snippet.description:
What did people in 1922 imagine life today would be like?  This newspaper article from May 7, 1922 will give you all the answers.

Isn't it fun to read past predictions of the future? It's not always all about flying cars and the like. Some of the issues discussed in such predictions are very thought-provoking. It's especially heartbreaking to learn that we have seriously underdelivered on basic topics. However, it's not all doom and gloom. There's always something to laugh about, too!

Please let us know in the comments if you enjoy this type of content. We'll make sure to bring you more of it!

snippet.title: Paris in Springtime - c.1922 | AI Enhanced Colorized Film w/sound
snippet.description:
Time travel back 100 years to the Paris markets on April 20th 1922. AI colorized and upscaled to 4k 60 fps clarity with added sound for an immersive experience.

Filmed along the Bouquinistes (book stalls) and Paris Flea markets, Les Halles. Today these same stalls ply their trade along the banks of the Seine.  We also glimpse various artists at work along the embankment.

Using AI neural networks, this silent film is now enhanced to 4K 60fps and with an immersive soundtrack.

Published by GlamourDaze 
by kind permission of the University of South Carolina.
AI enhancement by GlamourDaze.com

Colorized using Deep Exemplar-based Video Colorization
https://arxiv.org/abs/1807.06587

Filmed on April 20th, 1922.
